<div class="playbook-container">
    <div class="playbook-header">
        <h1>📧 Newsletter Playbook</h1>
        <p>Complete strategy, templates, and sequences for the Behavior School newsletter. Based on B2B email best practices for professional audiences.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Quick Metrics -->
    <div class="section-card">
        <h2>📊 Target Metrics</h2>
        <div class="metric-grid">
            <div class="metric-box">
                <div class="value">42%+</div>
                <div class="label">Open Rate</div>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-box">
                <div class="value">3-4%</div>
                <div class="label">Click Rate</div>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-box">
                <div class="value">&lt;0.3%</div>
                <div class="label">Unsubscribe</div>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-box">
                <div class="value">Tue 6:30a</div>
                <div class="label">Send Time (PT)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-box">
                <div class="value">&lt;3 min</div>
                <div class="label">Read Time</div>
            </div>
            <div class="metric-box">
                <div class="value">30-40</div>
                <div class="label">Subject Chars</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Weekly Template -->
    <div class="section-card">
        <h2>📝 Weekly Digest Template</h2>
        <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyTemplate('weekly-template')">Copy Template</button>
        <p>The "One Big Thing" format. 200-350 words core content, under 3 minutes to read.</p>
        
        <div class="template-box" id="weekly-template">Subject: [40 chars max, value-first]
Preview: [Extends the subject line, 40-90 chars]

---

Hey [First Name],

[1-2 sentences of context. Why this topic matters this week.]

---

## [This Week's Topic Title]

[200-350 words of practical, actionable content.

Structure: Problem → Insight → Action Step

Use short paragraphs (2-3 sentences max).
Include one specific example or scenario.
End with a clear "try this" action.]

---

### Quick Hits

→ [Link title]: [One-line description]
→ [Link title]: [One-line description]  
→ [Link title]: [One-line description]

---

[Soft CTA: "If you're prepping for the BCBA exam, we just 
added 200 new practice questions. Check them out here."]

— Rob

---
Unsubscribe | Update preferences
Behavior School LLC | behaviorschool.com</div>

        <h3>4-Week Content Rotation</h3>
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Week</th>
                    <th>Category</th>
                    <th>Example Topics</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge badge-green">Week 1</span></td>
                    <td>Practical Strategy</td>
                    <td>FBA shortcuts, classroom data collection systems</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge badge-blue">Week 2</span></td>
                    <td>Research Spotlight</td>
                    <td>New study translated to plain language</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Week 3</span></td>
                    <td>Career/Professional</td>
                    <td>Supervision tips, advocacy, salary data</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="badge badge-green">Week 4</span></td>
                    <td>Tool/Template</td>
                    <td>Free downloadable (data sheet, checklist)</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Subject Lines -->
    <div class="section-card">
        <h2>✍️ Subject Line Formulas</h2>
        <p><strong>Target:</strong> 30-40 characters (7 words or fewer). Front-load the value.</p>
        
        <ul class="formula-list">
            <li>
                <span class="formula">Specific number + outcome</span>
                <span class="example">"3 FBA shortcuts for school teams"</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="formula">Question the reader has</span>
                <span class="example">"Is your BIP actually being followed?"</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="formula">This week's actionable tip</span>
                <span class="example">"Try this before your next IEP meeting"</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="formula">Curated resource</span>
                <span class="example">"The data sheet template I use daily"</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <span class="formula">Contrarian/surprising</span>
                <span class="example">"Stop graphing everything"</span>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What to Avoid</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>ALL CAPS or excessive punctuation</li>
            <li>"Newsletter #47" or "Monthly Update" (zero value)</li>
            <li>Clickbait that doesn't deliver</li>
            <li>Emojis (test carefully with professionals)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Welcome Sequence -->
    <div class="section-card">
        <h2>👋 Welcome Sequence (5 Emails, 10 Days)</h2>
        <p>Goal: Deliver immediate value, set expectations, soft-introduce the product.</p>
        
        <div class="email-sequence">
            <div class="email-card">
                <div class="day">Email 1 — Immediate (within 1 minute)</div>
                <div class="subject">Subject: Here's your [lead magnet name]</div>
                <div class="purpose">Purpose: Deliver the promised resource + set expectations</div>
                <div class="outline">
• Deliver the lead magnet (download link, prominent)
• "I'm Rob. I build tools for BCBAs in schools."
• What to expect: "Every Tuesday, you'll get one practical tip you can use that week."
• Sign-off: "Talk soon, — Rob"
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="email-card">
                <div class="day">Email 2 — Day 2</div>
                <div class="subject">Subject: The one thing I wish I knew as a new district BCBA</div>
                <div class="purpose">Purpose: Build personal connection + credibility</div>
                <div class="outline">
• Short personal story (3-4 paragraphs max)
• One actionable takeaway related to the story
• No product mention
• Invite reply: "What's your biggest challenge right now?"
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="email-card">
                <div class="day">Email 3 — Day 4</div>
                <div class="subject">Subject: [Specific useful content related to lead magnet]</div>
                <div class="purpose">Purpose: Deliver more value, build the "worth opening" habit</div>
                <div class="outline">
• Teach something complementary to the lead magnet
• Include a mini case study or example
• Link to a relevant blog post
• No product mention
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="email-card">
                <div class="day">Email 4 — Day 7</div>
                <div class="subject">Subject: How I built [product name] (and why)</div>
                <div class="purpose">Purpose: Introduce the product through origin story</div>
                <div class="outline">
• Origin story: what problem prompted building the tool
• How it works (brief, 2-3 sentences)
• Who it's for (and who it's NOT for)
• Link: "See how it works" (not "Buy now")
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="email-card">
                <div class="day">Email 5 — Day 10</div>
                <div class="subject">Subject: You're officially on the Tuesday list</div>
                <div class="purpose">Purpose: Transition to weekly newsletter</div>
                <div class="outline">
• "Starting next Tuesday, you'll get the weekly email"
• Recap the format they'll receive
• Preference center link for adjustments
• Soft CTA: mention product with specific benefit
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Welcome Sequence Targets</h3>
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Metric</th>
                    <th>Target</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>Email 1 open rate</td><td>60%+</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Lead magnet click rate (Email 1)</td><td>70%+</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Reply rate (Email 2)</td><td>2-5%</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Sequence completion (open Email 5)</td><td>60%+</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Total unsubscribes across sequence</td><td>&lt;2%</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Lead Magnets -->
    <div class="section-card">
        <h2>🎁 Lead Magnets (by Expected Conversion)</h2>
        <table>
